| Addition | Reason |
|---|---|
| NSIS Windows-only | `desktop:build:nsis*` on Linux/macOS would fail; agents on non-Windows hosts need to know this |
| `desktop:dev:raw` purpose | Explicitly documented in CONTRIBUTING.md but absent from AGENTS.md; useful for OpenSSL debugging |
| `build:web` = three steps | Agents might run `type-check:web` then `build:web` redundantly |
| `prebuild` auto-hook | Agents who discover `prebuild` might call it manually before `desktop:build`, unaware it's automatic |
| Tauri devtools always-on | Gives agents context for frontend debugging shortcuts without needing to search CONTRIBUTING.md |
| mobile-web `dist` workaround | Discovered from CI; an agent might "fix" this as a missing step and generate an unnecessary build |